==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ariel
<hw>A"ri*el</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Heb.
<ets>ari⟦eum⟧l</ets>, perh. confused with E.
<ets>a⟦eum⟧rial</ets>.]</ety> <def>In the Cabala, a water spirit; in
later folklore, a light and graceful spirit of the air.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ In Zoology, <xex>ariel</xex> is used adjectively of
certain birds noted for their graceful flight; <as>as, the
<ex>ariel</ex> toucan; the <ex>ariel</ex> petrel</as>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aries</ent>⟦br⟧
